ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you haven't taken a DB course, 537 will be a great choice. If you have, then there's nothing new.
Yes. If you have the background.
it is good for anyone who want to learn database without any basic knowledge of database
Good course. Would recommend it for people looking to get into databases for the first time. Wouldn't recommend it for people who already have a working knowledge of some database system.
Yes. But if one wants more advanced coverage, then this course is not suitable.
I would strongly recommend CS 537 to all students of CS.I would term it as a FUN course!
I would definitely recommend the course. Anyone with or without a computer science background can clearly understand what databases are all about.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It provides me a overall view of the database world, including the current issues, basic database concepts. It is quite amazing that I can learn all that in one single semester.
Deepened my knowledge about the theory behind database design but not really the applications
General knowledge of the DB field.
Very helpful for looking for a job in database
